  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Problem\n\nWhen sending funds via chat command, the UI requires you to select a wallet to send from before entering an amount.\n\nIf you do this in the wrong order, as prompted if following the flow from top to bottom of the screen, you will receive an `Insufficient funds` error. \n\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/71679354-5f25bc00-2d55-11ea-82e6-0237129e2e51.png)\n\n## Implementation\n\nHow can we improve this? \n\n- Restrict user from entering amount until account is selected\n- Highlight account selector on the screen\n- Reverse the order of amount and account selector\n- [Update the error copy to be more instructive](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/9742#issuecomment-570605945)\n\nI think this requires your input @andmironov & @yenda - not a v1 blocker but it's fairly confusing.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nWe need to agree upon a solution before determining acceptance criteria.",
